'''Tim Veekhoven''' (born [[May 5]], [[1976]])<ref name="Birth" /> has contributed to [[StarWars.com]], the [[Star Wars Blog]], ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'', ''[[Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon]]'', and [[Star Wars Encyclopedia (series)|Star Wars Encyclopedia]] from [[De Agostini]].

==Biography==
Tim Veekhoven is the author of the backstories of [[Swilla Corey]], [[Tzizvvt]], [[Maxiron Agolerga/Legends|Maxiron Agolerga]] and [[Wam Lufba/Legends|Wam Lufba]] appearing in the [[Databank (original)|original Databank]], through the ''[[What's The Story?]]'' feature of [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

He is co-founder and president of TeeKay-421, the Belgian ''Star Wars'' fan club, and Administrator of Yodapedia, the Dutch/Flemish ''Star Wars'' wiki. In September 2012 he was honored as a ''Friend of the Rebellion'' and in 2015 an ''Honorary Member'' by [[Rebel Legion|Rebel Legion Benelux]].

At [[Celebration Europe II]] he participated at the ''International Star Wars Fandom'' panel with [[Gerald Home]] on Friday and organized the ''Star Wars Trivia Challenge'' with TeeKay-421 on Sunday.

Together with Kevin Beentjes and [[Sander de Lange]], he researched and wrote for the [[Rogues Gallery (department)|Rogues Gallery]] feature in ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'', starting with issue [[Star Wars Insider 145|145]].

His alias is {{U|Sompeetalay}} on [[Wookieepedia]].

